This paper deals with the problem of maintaining accurate query results on large datasets using materialized views, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The proposed solution involves data cleaning techniques, which are also relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of outlier indexing to handle skewed data distributions suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), while the evaluation of the method using a generated dataset and a real-world application involves statistical analysis and machine learning (cs.LG).
